rk804V0HpQ6u9sZ0tBeg==","shasum":"fa4794627bf455a47c4f56881d8a6132d581ffdb","tarball":"https://registry.npmjs.org/shallow-compare/-/shallow-compare-1.2.2.tgz","signatures":[{"keyid":"SHA256:jl3bwswu80PjjokCgh0o2w5c2U4LhQAE57gj9cz1kzA","sig":"MEYCIQDcna0PgUA1nwtn3sOVGdfHP8NbHLi6iEMu4hYA6qqNAQIhAPCbYxOGxmAq/j2cT/yYqi8KFdkM5liFVCdCKAUCuogf"}]},"maintainers":[{"name":"tkh44","email":"kye.hohenberger@gmail.com"}],"_npmOperationalInternal":{"host":"s3://npm-registry-packages","tmp":"tmp/shallow-compare-1.2.2.tgz_1506627727324_0.4244085580576211"}}},"readme":"# shallow-compare\n\n[![npm version](https://badge.fury.io/js/shallow-compare.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/js/shallow-compare)\n\nStand alone shallowCompare for use in libraries that support shouldComponentUpdate\n\n## API\n\n`shallowCompare(instance, nextProps, nextState)`\n\n - instance (_component instance_) - the component's instance (`this`)\n - nextProps (_object_) - the next props\n - nextState (_object_) - the next state\n \n## Example\n```javascript\nclass Foo extends Component {\n  constructor (props) {\n    super(props);\n    this.state = { color: 'blue' }\n  }\n\n  shouldComponentUpdate (nextProps, nextState) {\n    return shallowCompare(this, nextProps, nextState)\n  }\n\n  render () {\n    return (\n      <div>{this.state.color}</div>\n    )\n  }\n}\n```\n","maintainers":[{"name":"tkh44","email":"kye.hohenberger@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2022-06-26T18:34:59.903Z","created":"2016-10-27T15:31:18.115Z","1.2.0":"2016-10-27T15:31:18.115Z","1.2.1":"2017-03-20T19:38:01.200Z","1.2.2":"2017-09-28T19:42:08.256Z"},"keywords":["react-component"],"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"README.md","users":{"jacob-beltran":true},"homepage":"https://github.com/tkh44/shallow-compare#readme","repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/tkh44/shallow-compare.git"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/tkh44/shallow-compare/issues"}}